---
layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "text-divider"
description: "Horizontal divider with centered text. Use to separate content sections or provide alternative action labels."
elementName: text-divider
category: custom
currentPath: /docs/elements/custom-elements/text-divider/
permalink: /docs/elements/custom-elements/text-divider/
---

{% set basicCode %}<text-divider>or</text-divider>{% endset %}

{% set formUsageCode %}<form>
  <layout-stack data-layout-gap="m">
    <form-field>
      <label for="email">Email</label>
      <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required />
    </form-field>

    <button type="submit">Continue with email</button>

    <text-divider>or continue with</text-divider>

    <layout-cluster data-layout-justify="center">
      <button type="button">Google</button>
      <button type="button">GitHub</button>
    </layout-cluster>
  </layout-stack>
</form>{% endset %}

{% set sectionUsageCode %}<article>
  <h2>Getting Started</h2>
  <p>Introduction content...</p>

  <text-divider>Chapter 1</text-divider>

  <p>Chapter content...</p>
</article>{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The <code>text-divider</code> element creates a horizontal line with centered text. Common uses include separating form sections ("or"), chapter markers, and content transitions.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <p>This element has no custom attributes. It's styled purely through CSS.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/text-divider-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/text-divider"
      title="Basic text divider"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic text divider">{{ basicCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>In Forms</h2>
    <p>Common pattern for login/signup forms to separate primary and alternative actions.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/text-divider-form.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/text-divider/form"
      title="Text divider in a form"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Form with text divider">{{ formUsageCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Content Sections</h2>
    <p>Use to mark transitions between content sections.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/text-divider-sections.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/text-divider/sections"
      title="Text divider between content sections"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Section divider">{{ sectionUsageCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Variations</h2>
    <p>The text content can be anything meaningful for the context.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/text-divider-variations.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/text-divider/variations"
      title="Text divider variations"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The divider is purely decorative - screen readers will read the text content naturally</li>
      <li>Avoid using the divider for critical navigation or structural purposes</li>
      <li>Keep text concise and meaningful</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
